202
00:19:18,960 --> 00:19:23,351
There's nowhere we can hide,
but somewhere there...

203
00:19:24,520 --> 00:19:29,071
... there's someone in the rain
looking for you!

204
00:19:35,760 --> 00:19:36,954
Michael!

205
00:19:37,640 --> 00:19:39,119
Michael!

206
00:19:41,200 --> 00:19:42,997
There's something missing.

207
00:19:43,840 --> 00:19:46,798
I know! There was a piano there.

208
00:19:47,320 --> 00:19:51,233
- Maybe we saw it in our dream?
- And the camp-bed too?

209
00:19:53,640 --> 00:19:54,789
Jane!

210
00:19:57,160 --> 00:20:01,073
Look, the piano!

211
00:20:03,960 --> 00:20:06,394
- Is the camp-bed there?
- It is.

212
00:20:12,280 --> 00:20:15,158
Mary Poppins, it's wonderful
you hadn't left.

213
00:20:16,080 --> 00:20:18,275
We almost thought you were
a dream.

214
00:20:18,560 --> 00:20:21,836
And your camp-bed. Where did
you sleep tonight?

215
00:20:22,120 --> 00:20:27,148
Gentlemen never ask ladies
questions like that.

216
00:20:28,800 --> 00:20:30,233
Hey!

217
00:20:31,760 --> 00:20:34,399
Mister Hey, please take my
camp-bed...

218
00:20:34,640 --> 00:20:36,870
... and put it in the nursery.
- Are you talking to me?

219
00:20:37,120 --> 00:20:41,033
Well didn't I say it clearly:
Mister Hey? - I'll do it.

220
00:20:41,320 --> 00:20:43,629
Only my name is Robert
Robertson. - Is that so?

221
00:20:44,400 --> 00:20:46,356
Well can't do anything
about it now.

222
00:20:46,520 --> 00:20:49,432
If I called you Mister Hey once,
you will have to be Mister Hey.

223
00:20:49,640 --> 00:20:53,758
Be careful! I sleep only on this
bed, and on nothing else.

224
00:20:54,000 --> 00:20:55,991
- Good morning, miss Poppins.
- Good morning.

225
00:20:56,280 --> 00:20:58,635
- Nasty weather, isn't it?
- It depends.

226
00:20:58,920 --> 00:21:01,229
At least for those who
save gasoline...

227
00:21:01,360 --> 00:21:03,590
... and ride to the office
on a bicycle.

228
00:21:06,400 --> 00:21:10,996
Mary! I must rush off to the
meeting of the "Women's League".

229
00:21:11,760 --> 00:21:14,069
The children are getting dressed.
Will you feed them please?

230
00:21:14,320 --> 00:21:16,151
Did you think I would let
them starve?

231
00:21:16,560 --> 00:21:19,120
And if you would be so kind as
to make a few purchases...

232
00:21:19,400 --> 00:21:22,358
Maybe. Maybe not.

233
00:21:22,760 --> 00:21:25,194
In any case show me, where I
can find the pram.

234
00:21:25,480 --> 00:21:27,232
You mean, the cart?

235
00:21:27,800 --> 00:21:31,509
My brother is so clumsy, he took
it for a chair and sat on it.

236
00:21:31,760 --> 00:21:34,797
I'm talking about Jane's
and Michael's old pram.

