342
00:29:54,000 --> 00:29:55,797
I'm switching off the light.

343
00:30:06,520 --> 00:30:09,717
- Do you often do that?
- Do what?

344
00:30:10,360 --> 00:30:12,476
Do you often jump about like
that?

345
00:30:13,240 --> 00:30:17,552
Jump about?! Would you kindly
explain what you mean?

346
00:30:17,920 --> 00:30:20,070
But we saw it just now!

347
00:30:20,720 --> 00:30:22,312
What?!

348
00:30:24,720 --> 00:30:26,950
- You saw me jump about?
- We did.

349
00:30:29,000 --> 00:30:30,638
How dare you!

350
00:30:31,680 --> 00:30:35,355
For your information, young man
I don't jump about, I dance.

351
00:30:35,880 --> 00:30:39,759
I finished a ballet school on
the Island of Tarabar.

352
00:30:40,200 --> 00:30:42,760
And with excellent marks!
Madam Corry's class.

353
00:30:49,520 --> 00:30:51,829
What a strange fantasy!
"Jump about"!

354
00:33:21,680 --> 00:33:23,477
Good morning, boys!

355
00:33:23,960 --> 00:33:25,871
I hope you had a good night's
sleep?

356
00:33:28,160 --> 00:33:31,072
Now for the musical class.

357
00:33:32,480 --> 00:33:33,959
Switch it on.

358
00:34:10,360 --> 00:34:13,238
It's a good thing you finally
agreed, Banks. My sources,

359
00:34:13,520 --> 00:34:18,036
very reliable sources say, they
will be flying in any time now.

360
00:34:18,480 --> 00:34:21,074
I am happy to use your advice,
admiral.

361
00:34:21,440 --> 00:34:22,475
Begin.

362
00:34:23,880 --> 00:34:24,915
Go ahead!

363
00:34:29,520 --> 00:34:31,875
- What's going on here? Stop!
- Stop!

364
00:34:32,920 --> 00:34:37,118
Good morning, Mrs. Banks. I am
Bob Gudetti from West-Mole Co.

365
00:34:38,400 --> 00:34:39,594
My assistant.

366
00:34:41,560 --> 00:34:42,675
Over my dead body!

367
00:34:43,240 --> 00:34:48,712
On the contrary, we are doing
all in our power to avoid that

368
00:34:49,120 --> 00:34:51,634
... in view of the possible
invasion from outer space.

369
00:34:52,760 --> 00:34:57,914
A quarter-de luxe class shelter
with a phone, a toilet and gas!

370
00:34:58,640 --> 00:35:00,949
Food supplies enough to last
8 years!

371
00:35:01,400 --> 00:35:03,868
With frugal rationing,
of course.

372
00:35:05,440 --> 00:35:09,752
- On what money, you fool?
- Safety is more important!

373
00:35:10,680 --> 00:35:12,477
Bravo, Banks. You did the
right thing.

374
00:35:12,960 --> 00:35:15,349
Hey, Boom, is this your
plotting?

375
00:35:17,040 --> 00:35:18,951
I'll show you what's what,
you rioter!

376
00:35:19,160 --> 00:35:21,071
- Militarist!
- Sponger!

377
00:35:21,600 --> 00:35:24,990
Today we shall take a sample
of the soil. Launch it!

378
00:35:41,960 --> 00:35:43,109
Stop!

379
00:35:43,680 --> 00:35:50,153
Hey you, foolish scoundrels!
I'll get you underground!

380
00:35:51,080 --> 00:35:54,959
Mister Banks, did you find oil?

381
00:35:56,320 --> 00:36:00,950
I hate to interfere, mister
Banks...

382
00:36:01,760 --> 00:36:04,228
... but I demand that you don't
disrupt our classes.

383
00:36:04,840 --> 00:36:07,195
Are you going to drill an
oil well?

384
00:36:07,480 --> 00:36:10,119
- No, this is different.
- Mind you, mister Banks:

385
00:36:10,400 --> 00:36:13,472
If you drill an oil well
and find oil,

386
00:36:13,760 --> 00:36:16,877
you may join the Organization
of Oil-exporting Countries.

387
00:36:17,440 --> 00:36:20,159
- I'm not afraid of threats!
- What shall we do?

388
00:36:20,440 --> 00:36:23,034
If you ignore considerations
of your family's peace,

389
00:36:23,680 --> 00:36:26,513
... you could at least think
about the environment.

390
00:36:26,920 --> 00:36:30,754
- I'm with you, sister!
- So what do we do then?

391
00:36:31,440 --> 00:36:33,795
- Who has the decisive word?
- You do!

392
00:36:33,960 --> 00:36:35,279
- Drill it here!
- Right here?

393
00:36:35,400 --> 00:36:37,231
- Yes!
- Take that idiot away!

394
00:36:38,040 --> 00:36:40,474
We'll see who wins! What, you
can't do it? Right!

395
00:36:40,760 --> 00:36:42,398
- Good morning.
- Hey!

396
00:36:43,600 --> 00:36:45,716
Oh, it's you, Mary Poppins!

397
00:36:46,000 --> 00:36:48,798
You are just about the only
sensible person in this house.

398
00:36:49,200 --> 00:36:53,478
You don't believe this nonsense
with aliens. Tell them!

399
00:36:53,960 --> 00:36:56,394
I think the earth is cold
today, sir.

400
00:36:57,200 --> 00:37:00,237
So you're in it too!

401
00:37:00,960 --> 00:37:04,873
Hey you! Are you or are you
not with them?

402
00:37:05,360 --> 00:37:08,636
I'm with the children, sir.
And we are going to the park.

403
00:37:09,120 --> 00:37:12,396
I would stand up from the ground
if I were you, mister Hey.

404
00:37:12,640 --> 00:37:15,473
What kind of an example are you
setting to your nephews?

405
00:37:45,600 --> 00:37:48,353
Don't break the rules!
Throw garbage into waist-bins!

406
00:37:49,160 --> 00:37:52,197
- No littering in the park!
- Don't litter with words, sir.

407
00:38:19,280 --> 00:38:21,589
Neley looks so happy today.

408
00:38:21,920 --> 00:38:24,957
And mister Willkins is sitting
on Mary's favorite place.

409
00:38:25,360 --> 00:38:27,954
All right, I will go to the
pavilion.

410
00:38:35,040 --> 00:38:39,158
But mister Willkins, I haven't
finished reading about Bill.

411
00:38:45,480 --> 00:38:46,833
Excuse me.

412
00:38:50,240 --> 00:38:53,391
I beg your pardon, did you say
something?

413
00:38:53,800 --> 00:38:56,519
Of course I did. I wanted to
read it to the end to find out,

414
00:38:56,760 --> 00:38:59,354
... what Astute Bill needed
the master-key for.

415
00:38:59,680 --> 00:39:03,116
Sorry, I can't help you. I
always finish reading at 4...

416
00:39:04,200 --> 00:39:07,397
... to get home in time for tea.

417
00:39:07,920 --> 00:39:10,753
Then maybe you can lend me your
magazine?

418
00:39:12,320 --> 00:39:14,914
Neley, I can tell you
about Bill.

419
00:39:15,360 --> 00:39:17,157
- Really, Jane?
- Yes.

420
00:39:17,480 --> 00:39:20,313
No, I have a coat and boots
on me...

421
00:39:20,920 --> 00:39:26,074
... and the young gentleman
must be very cold.

422
00:39:26,960 --> 00:39:29,155
I will give him my magazine.

423
00:39:29,440 --> 00:39:31,237
Don't worry, mister Willkins.

424
00:39:31,560 --> 00:39:34,028
In a week the series about Bill
will be shown on TV.

425
00:39:34,320 --> 00:39:39,075
Never! I am categorically
against screen versions!

426
00:39:39,880 --> 00:39:41,598
Thank you, mister Willkins.

427
00:39:47,800 --> 00:39:50,837
So this is what water is like!
Cool and light!

428
00:39:52,240 --> 00:39:56,279
People, you are so lucky that
you can walk on the ground!

429
00:39:56,600 --> 00:39:58,113
It is so wonderful, Jane!

430
00:39:58,720 --> 00:40:01,075
I'd say this is absolutely
revolting.

431
00:40:02,080 --> 00:40:04,196
Good day, Mary Poppins.

432
00:40:06,160 --> 00:40:09,994
Who allowed you to come down
here, may I ask?

433
00:40:10,200 --> 00:40:13,112
No one. My legs jumped down on
their own, Mary Poppins.

434
00:40:13,520 --> 00:40:17,559
Well then they'd better
jump up again.

435
00:40:18,600 --> 00:40:20,591
Shame on you! On an odd date,

436
00:40:20,920 --> 00:40:24,037
... when Saturn is hardly seen,
and the Hound Dogs don't bark?

437
00:40:25,040 --> 00:40:26,473
What did they teach you?

438
00:40:27,120 --> 00:40:30,351
Mary Poppins! Please let him
spend some more time with us.

439
00:40:30,720 --> 00:40:32,073
A little more!

440
00:40:32,480 --> 00:40:37,508
He must feel so lonely standing
there with no one to talk to!

441
00:40:38,360 --> 00:40:40,749
Please, Marry Poppins! Please!

442
00:40:42,160 --> 00:40:46,199
Edward! What's with you? What
a ridiculous show?

443
00:40:46,760 --> 00:40:49,228
Get up from the dirty grass!

444
00:40:49,680 --> 00:40:52,148
It is all your influence! You..!

445
00:40:52,600 --> 00:40:56,752
- Plebeian! Half-bred! Monster!
- Calm down, Mrs. Lark.

446
00:40:57,240 --> 00:40:59,196
Ed! Bartholomew!

447
00:40:59,960 --> 00:41:01,313
Bartholomew!

448
00:41:02,720 --> 00:41:05,439
Bartholomew! Wait, Bartholomew!

449
00:41:07,480 --> 00:41:09,755
- Bartholomew!
- Come here!

450
00:41:10,160 --> 00:41:11,559
Bartholomew!

451
00:41:12,160 --> 00:41:15,914
We came out for a walk before
tea. It's such a lovely day!

452
00:41:16,320 --> 00:41:18,117
And the dogs insisted.

453
00:41:18,880 --> 00:41:20,871
My God, what am I seeing?

454
00:41:21,360 --> 00:41:26,036
You heartless mean little boy!
Why torture the poor fish?

455
00:41:27,600 --> 00:41:31,070
Put it back where you caught it
this instant!

456
00:41:31,400 --> 00:41:33,072
I'm afraid It is quite
impossible.

457
00:41:35,200 --> 00:41:36,997
It's too far away.

458
00:41:37,240 --> 00:41:41,870
That doesn't matter. You can't
torture helpless creatures!

459
00:41:42,400 --> 00:41:45,198
I'm going to tell this to the
constable!

460
00:41:46,120 --> 00:41:47,838
Bartholomew, what odd jumps?

461
00:41:48,480 --> 00:41:51,597
- What a scandalous dog!
- You are impossible!

462
00:41:52,400 --> 00:41:53,674
What is he saying?

463
00:41:54,760 --> 00:41:57,672
He says, he won't take that.

464
00:41:58,120 --> 00:42:01,476
He insists that you speak with
him in a polite tone.

465
00:42:02,600 --> 00:42:04,875
I'm going to complain to
the Prime-minister.

466
00:42:06,360 --> 00:42:09,909
Neley, you have 10 minutes.

467
00:42:10,320 --> 00:42:11,833
And then?

468
00:42:36,640 --> 00:42:37,959
Beautiful.

469
00:42:38,440 --> 00:42:41,591
It is live music, isn't it,
Mary Poppins?

470
00:42:54,760 --> 00:42:57,957
Miss Jane, I don't know if
there will be...

471
00:42:58,280 --> 00:43:00,669
... another beautiful day
like today in my life,

472
00:43:01,000 --> 00:43:03,753
but I know for sure, I will
never forgive myself...

473
00:43:04,080 --> 00:43:06,435
if now I don't have the courage
to ask you to a waltz.

474
00:43:06,720 --> 00:43:08,119
I will be honored.

475
00:43:08,320 --> 00:43:11,551
Michael, I ask you as a friend:
please hold my dolphin.

476
00:43:12,880 --> 00:43:14,074
Thank you.

477
00:43:24,120 --> 00:43:26,475
Jane, I don't know how
to dance waltz.

478
00:43:27,720 --> 00:43:30,029
Then why did you ask me?

479
00:43:32,160 --> 00:43:35,152
Well then, let's just walk
a little.

480
00:43:35,600 --> 00:43:37,192
Thank you so much.

481
00:43:40,160 --> 00:43:44,073
- How do you know Mary Poppins?
- She's a friend of my father's.

482
00:43:44,400 --> 00:43:46,755
Who is your father?
Where does he live?

483
00:43:47,800 --> 00:43:52,316
He stands on a cliff over the
sea with a trident and a horn...

484
00:43:53,080 --> 00:43:56,117
and my mother sits next to him
and brushes her hair.

485
00:43:56,560 --> 00:43:59,028
And the seagulls circle
above them,

486
00:43:59,320 --> 00:44:02,153
and cast winged shadows on their
marble bodies.

487
00:44:02,720 --> 00:44:06,156
How beautiful! By why did
you leave them?

488
00:44:06,440 --> 00:44:10,069
I didn't want to. But what can
statues do against people?

489
00:44:11,720 --> 00:44:14,029
How did you get to our
garden?

490
00:44:14,320 --> 00:44:16,709
In a box. We always travel
like that.

491
00:44:17,320 --> 00:44:20,517
They need us in parks,
museums and gardens.

492
00:44:20,760 --> 00:44:23,115
And they buy us and send
us in parcels.

493
00:44:25,880 --> 00:44:29,634
And it doesn't occur to anyone
that we may be lonely.

494
00:44:30,480 --> 00:44:32,710
I love you, Neley.

495
00:44:33,200 --> 00:44:35,430
I want you to stay with
us forever.

496
00:44:36,160 --> 00:44:37,798
I love you too.

497
00:44:38,880 --> 00:44:41,758
But it's impossible, I have to
get back to where I belong.

498
00:44:42,560 --> 00:44:43,788
I understand.

499
00:44:47,640 --> 00:44:50,279
Hey, Mary. How are you feeling?
Hope your back doesn't ache?

500
00:44:52,040 --> 00:44:54,110
Any news?

501
00:44:54,320 --> 00:44:56,993
I'm terribly hungry. Is there
anything yummy...

502
00:44:57,480 --> 00:45:00,074
... for an old friend.

503
00:45:00,320 --> 00:45:02,515
- I didn't hear "thank you".
- Come on, girl!

504
00:45:02,840 --> 00:45:06,276
No time for such ceremonies.
I had meetings all day...

505
00:45:06,960 --> 00:45:09,997
... consultations, negotiations,
discussions.

506
00:45:10,640 --> 00:45:12,631
A lot to decide, a lot to see.

507
00:45:12,840 --> 00:45:15,274
Will you be quiet? Stop
jabbering like a common sparrow.

508
00:45:16,360 --> 00:45:19,272
- You came from there?
- A I have an urgent message.

509
00:45:19,560 --> 00:45:23,189
There are two impossible spoilt
twins in New Zealand.

510
00:45:23,640 --> 00:45:26,871
- When?
- The wind changes at midnight.

511
00:45:27,760 --> 00:45:31,116
Well, I have to be off, my girl.
See you soon.

512
00:45:32,000 --> 00:45:34,036
See you soon, old chatterbox.

513
00:45:34,640 --> 00:45:37,552
The wind will change
at midnight!

514
00:45:37,960 --> 00:45:41,111
Wonderful! Isn't it strange...

515
00:45:42,400 --> 00:45:44,709
... that people don't fly.

516
00:45:47,120 --> 00:45:49,031
I had nothing to do with it,
constable.

517
00:45:50,040 --> 00:45:52,235
I never touched it,
I didn't even come near it!

518
00:45:52,520 --> 00:45:55,876
Nonsense, Smith! The statues
are your responsibility.

519
00:45:56,560 --> 00:45:58,596
And no one else could have
done that.

520
00:45:58,880 --> 00:46:02,793
I never had any luck, since
I was a little boy!

521
00:46:04,480 --> 00:46:06,994
- Listen, constable...
- We are wasting our time!

522
00:46:07,920 --> 00:46:11,549
First I have to look for a
naked boy who mistreats a fish!

523
00:46:11,920 --> 00:46:14,150
Was it a cod?.. What did
Mrs. Lark say?

524
00:46:14,320 --> 00:46:15,958
- A mackerel.
- All the more!

525
00:46:16,120 --> 00:46:19,590
Now they tell me they're missing
their most valuable statue!

526
00:46:20,320 --> 00:46:22,436
You disappointed me.

527
00:46:22,920 --> 00:46:25,388
I relied on you, and you...

528
00:46:25,840 --> 00:46:28,149
This is how you pay me
for my trust in you!

529
00:46:29,080 --> 00:46:30,638
Good gracious!

530
00:46:35,680 --> 00:46:38,956
Smith, why didn't you tell
me in the first place?

531
00:46:39,600 --> 00:46:43,036
A brilliant idea! Now you don't
have to pretend any more!

532
00:46:45,280 --> 00:46:48,716
Ladies and gentlemen, I was
unfair to the poor fellow.

533
00:46:49,160 --> 00:46:53,392
He proved he was not only a
watchman, but an artist as well.

534
00:46:53,840 --> 00:46:58,709
He furnished the statue with
a marble book. Excellent!

535
00:46:59,240 --> 00:47:02,710
It is our duty to encourage the
urge of the young to knowledge.

536
00:47:03,640 --> 00:47:05,073
What about the fish?

537
00:47:06,760 --> 00:47:10,036
You can get rid of it.

538
00:47:19,680 --> 00:47:22,513
Don't be sour, darling.

539
00:47:33,480 --> 00:47:36,074
When we decided to get married,
you told me:

540
00:47:36,480 --> 00:47:41,315
I want either a life of plenty,
or two charming kids.

541
00:47:41,600 --> 00:47:43,397
And you agreed.

542
00:47:43,880 --> 00:47:47,509
Well, now we have both
- a good house and two kids.

543
00:47:48,400 --> 00:47:53,428
What else do you need? What is
it you're chasing after?

544
00:47:54,960 --> 00:47:58,509
Everyone is chasing after
something.

545
00:47:59,520 --> 00:48:01,511
That's what life is all about,
isn't it?

546
00:48:01,880 --> 00:48:04,519
Maybe it's just that everyone
lives wrong?

547
00:48:04,920 --> 00:48:08,151
Everyone can't live wrong.
And we're not any different.

548
00:48:08,640 --> 00:48:11,598
Besides, that is child's talk.

549
00:48:12,680 --> 00:48:15,672
Look at Mary Poppins. She's
always calm and cool.

550
00:48:16,240 --> 00:48:20,028
If she weren't our nanny I'd say
she was perfection herself.

551
00:48:21,600 --> 00:48:24,068
And receiving such a small
salary at that.

552
00:48:40,240 --> 00:48:41,559
I wonder.

553
00:48:42,640 --> 00:48:44,278
What?

554
00:48:51,400 --> 00:48:56,554
I wonder if all this would have
happened, if you weren't here?

555
00:49:04,040 --> 00:49:05,553
And I wonder,

556
00:49:06,040 --> 00:49:09,669
when you stop being interested
in what is none of your concern.

557
00:49:10,000 --> 00:49:11,558
Go to bed now!

558
00:49:25,600 --> 00:49:28,558
I wonder, who I am?

559
00:49:28,840 --> 00:49:32,355
What kind of a question is that?
You are Jane Banks.

560
00:49:32,880 --> 00:49:34,438
And I am Michael Banks.

561
00:49:34,960 --> 00:49:36,473
Is that so, Mary Poppins?

562
00:49:37,080 --> 00:49:40,470
Maybe. How should I know? I'm
not the inquiry office.

563
00:49:45,000 --> 00:49:46,069
Your weapon!

564
00:49:47,080 --> 00:49:48,399
Get under the covers, quick!

565
00:49:52,960 --> 00:49:55,554
What did I say to make her
angry again?

566
00:49:57,240 --> 00:49:59,196
Mind you, sir...

567
00:50:00,160 --> 00:50:04,153
I never get angry. I have
royal patience.

568
00:50:05,120 --> 00:50:08,078
Only you can't shoot at people
from around the corner.

569
00:50:12,600 --> 00:50:17,674
And I am so kind today! What
a pity this day had to end.

570
00:50:18,120 --> 00:50:20,759
- Everything ends sometime.
- Except you.

571
00:50:21,120 --> 00:50:23,918
You won't leave us, will you?

572
00:50:27,520 --> 00:50:31,593
lmagine what a life I will have
if I spend it all on you.

573
00:50:34,160 --> 00:50:39,951
I wonder if mom and dad would
believe us if we told them?

574
00:50:40,360 --> 00:50:42,316
- Told them what?
- Everything.

575
00:50:43,000 --> 00:50:45,639
About Neley, and about Edward,
and Bartholomew.

576
00:50:47,120 --> 00:50:51,398
Only they wouldn't believe us.
And they will never know.

577
00:50:52,440 --> 00:50:54,908
- There was a time when
they knew. - Really?!

578
00:50:55,120 --> 00:50:57,315
You're saying, they knew
everything too?

579
00:50:57,560 --> 00:50:59,994
That Neley is alive, and that
you can fly,

580
00:51:00,320 --> 00:51:02,515
... and understand what dogs
are saying?

581
00:51:02,720 --> 00:51:07,350
Yes, they knew all that and the
language of birds and animals.

582
00:51:08,920 --> 00:51:10,035
In the past.

583
00:51:10,320 --> 00:51:13,392
- Then why did they forget it?
- Because they grew up.

584
00:51:15,280 --> 00:51:17,032
That's sad.

585
00:51:17,800 --> 00:51:19,518
None the less, it is true.

586
00:51:21,720 --> 00:51:23,073
I'm turning off the light.

587
00:51:23,320 --> 00:51:27,632
You are a grown-up too, but you
know it, you haven't forgotten.

588
00:51:28,280 --> 00:51:31,989
Me? I'm not like everyone else.

589
00:51:33,520 --> 00:51:37,991
I m a rare exception. I am
beyond comparison.

590
00:51:38,920 --> 00:51:42,071
I am "Lady Perfection".

591
00:51:47,720 --> 00:51:51,998
All right, a few more minutes,
as an exception.

592
00:51:56,800 --> 00:52:00,031
But on one condition: you will
go to sleep...

593
00:52:03,320 --> 00:52:05,311
... and you will have sweet
dreams.

594
00:52:14,600 --> 00:52:18,275
All that happened many
years ago...

595
00:52:21,480 --> 00:52:25,189
Is stored in our colorful
dreams,

596
00:52:28,880 --> 00:52:34,671
And the magic ring-dance
of those dreams...

597
00:52:36,160 --> 00:52:40,039
Takes grown-ups back into their
childhood.

598
00:52:41,480 --> 00:52:44,392
Dreams, where fairy-tales live
amidst wonders,

599
00:52:45,320 --> 00:52:51,156
Dreams, where you can reach out
and touch the stars,

600
00:52:52,640 --> 00:52:55,916
He, who is a little in his
childhood, is a happy man.

601
00:52:56,880 --> 00:52:59,633
Our childhood is long gone,

602
00:53:00,320 --> 00:53:03,278
the ABC book of our past life
is read to the last page.

