Our childish dreams.

625
00:55:12,720 --> 00:55:15,439
Good evening, Mary Poppins. That
was beautiful singing.

626
00:55:16,240 --> 00:55:17,434
Me?!

627
00:55:18,680 --> 00:55:21,274
I suggest that you wouldn't
forget, I am a decent girl...

628
00:55:21,920 --> 00:55:25,595
and I sing only in the morning!
- Then I must have dreamt it.

629
00:55:26,920 --> 00:55:30,515
I've been wanting to talk to you
all this time, Mary Poppins.

630
00:55:30,880 --> 00:55:33,269
- You're not in a hurry now?
- Indeed I am!

631
00:55:33,920 --> 00:55:37,674
- But it depends on the wind.
- The wind? It is getting cold.

632
00:55:39,080 --> 00:55:41,833
I think it is time that you
moved inside, mister Hey.

633
00:55:42,240 --> 00:55:45,232
Autumn is nearing, tents
catch fire.

634
00:55:46,280 --> 00:55:50,592
I see. So you too think I'm a
useless idler.

635
00:55:52,240 --> 00:55:56,233
On the contrary. I like you,
mister Hey.

636
00:55:56,640 --> 00:55:58,915
You like live music too,
don't you?

637
00:55:59,320 --> 00:56:02,437
- Live music?
- The one you don't turn on.

638
00:56:03,560 --> 00:56:04,834
Oh yes, I see.

639
00:56:05,080 --> 00:56:07,594
However some of your songs
are... how should I put it?

640
00:56:07,880 --> 00:56:10,599
But I hate to see how some folks
live on Cherry Street,

641
00:56:10,920 --> 00:56:12,831
... and I tell about it in
my songs.

642
00:56:13,160 --> 00:56:15,469
Did it ever occur to you,
mister Hey,..

643
00:56:15,680 --> 00:56:18,353
that at times people come to
understand it themselves?

644
00:56:21,640 --> 00:56:23,471
Yes. But what should I do then?

645
00:56:23,760 --> 00:56:26,194
Maybe, It's time I started
doing something indeed?

646
00:56:26,520 --> 00:56:29,159
I have to go too!

647
00:56:29,880 --> 00:56:34,158
Good bye, and don't forget what
I said about your nephews.

648
00:56:49,720 --> 00:56:52,234
Do something! Do something!

649
00:56:53,280 --> 00:56:57,034
Do something! That's it!
Why didn't it ever occur to me?

650
00:56:57,640 --> 00:57:01,599
You are damn right, Mary!
Only how do you do it?

651
00:57:03,000 --> 00:57:06,231
It's a pity you won't see how I
get into this car...

652
00:57:06,480 --> 00:57:10,393
... and dump it in the nearest
ditch, the damned gravedigger!

653
00:57:12,600 --> 00:57:13,794
No, that's not it.

654
00:57:14,200 --> 00:57:16,191
Only he who acts,
accomplishes things!

655
00:57:23,200 --> 00:57:24,553
No, that's not it again.

656
00:57:27,040 --> 00:57:30,430
What a pity you won't see this,
Mary. I think I won't either.

657
00:58:13,120 --> 00:58:14,314
Have they come?

658
00:58:14,680 --> 00:58:18,116
They're here! Pipe all hands
off deck!

659
00:58:18,960 --> 00:58:21,758
Full submersion!

660
00:58:22,320 --> 00:58:24,595
Full submersion! They're here!

661
00:58:24,840 --> 00:58:27,559
They've come, my beauties!
God damn my spleen!

662
00:58:39,960 --> 00:58:46,195
Post 107 reporting a fire at 17,
On Cherry St.! On the double!

663
00:58:46,560 --> 00:58:49,950
I knew it from the beginning,
just like Astute Bill!

664
00:58:50,280 --> 00:58:52,748
Post 107 reporting. There's a
fire at 17, Cherry Street!

665
00:58:53,160 --> 00:58:57,073
Mister Banks found an oil
deposit! Batten down the hatch!

666
00:58:57,240 --> 00:58:59,071
Calm down, the fire brigade
is on it's way.

667
00:58:59,200 --> 00:59:01,555
Do you have buckets, hooks,
fire-extinguishers?

668
00:59:02,200 --> 00:59:07,638
Congratulations, mister Banks!
What luck!

669
00:59:09,920 --> 00:59:11,478
It isn't oil, it's gas.

670
00:59:11,880 --> 00:59:13,438
- Gas?
- Gas?!

671
00:59:13,720 --> 00:59:17,156
That's not so bad, mister Banks.
Gas is even better than oil.

672
00:59:17,920 --> 00:59:21,390
It happens that you go to pick
berries and find a mushroom.

673
00:59:21,800 --> 00:59:24,837
The mushroom - that is gas - is
much better than oil.

674
00:59:25,120 --> 00:59:28,715
You stretch a gas pipeline
across my courtyard...

675
00:59:29,280 --> 00:59:35,833
and join the Organization of
Gas-exporting Countries.

676
00:59:36,560 --> 00:59:39,358
Darling, did I get lucky
at last?

677
01:00:01,000 --> 01:00:03,878
Quiet! Quiet! If they ask,
I was with you.

678
01:00:04,280 --> 01:00:05,599
What is that? A thunderstorm?

679
01:00:05,880 --> 01:00:08,235
- Oh, no. A little fire.
- Hurray!

680
01:00:08,680 --> 01:00:12,150
Quiet, children! We were
playing "hit-ship".

681
01:00:12,400 --> 01:00:15,597
Hurray! Jane, look, our house
is on fire! Hurray!

682
01:00:15,920 --> 01:00:18,115
- Where is Mary Poppins?
- Jane, look...

683
01:00:20,160 --> 01:00:24,119
And where's the piano by "Madam
Corry"? And the camp-bed?

684
01:00:26,920 --> 01:00:29,309
The wind! The wind has changed!

685
01:00:30,000 --> 01:00:32,673
That means.. that means,
she's gone?

686
01:00:34,040 --> 01:00:39,160
She said she would stay until
the wind changed direction.

687
01:00:40,440 --> 01:00:43,000
Thank God you're here!

688
01:00:44,120 --> 01:00:46,429
We were playing "hit-ship".

689
01:00:48,040 --> 01:00:50,395
- Mother, she's gone!
- Who?

690
01:00:50,920 --> 01:00:53,036
Mother, Mary Poppins left us.

691
01:00:53,800 --> 01:00:57,873
To leave at such a crucial
moment? How selfish of her!

692
01:00:58,440 --> 01:01:02,149
I will never accept the
heartless girl back. Never!

693
01:01:02,440 --> 01:01:04,908
- Mother!
- You are so wicked!

694
01:01:05,720 --> 01:01:09,508
Shame on you, children.

695
01:01:10,120 --> 01:01:13,908
I want Mary Poppins, and no
one else in the whole world!

696
01:01:14,200 --> 01:01:15,872
Where is the fire hydrant?

697
01:01:16,120 --> 01:01:18,793
My God, well it isn't in the
nursery!

698
01:01:27,080 --> 01:01:28,399
Look!

699
01:01:29,760 --> 01:01:31,034
Oh!

700
01:01:33,520 --> 01:01:37,069
It's her. It's her portrait.

701
01:01:38,400 --> 01:01:43,713
There's something written there.
It's "Au revoir, Mary Poppins".

702
01:01:44,160 --> 01:01:46,435
- Au revo...
- Hey, what's "Au revoir"?

703
01:01:47,520 --> 01:01:51,274
I think it's in French and I
think it's "Farewell".

704
01:01:52,160 --> 01:01:53,388
No!

705
01:01:54,240 --> 01:01:56,674
It's "good-bye". I'm sure.
It's "good-bye"!

706
01:01:57,000 --> 01:01:59,275
- Then it's all right?
- She will come back!

707
01:01:59,640 --> 01:02:01,915
She always keeps her promise!

708
01:02:07,520 --> 01:02:09,317
- Oh, mister Banks.
- Yes?

709
01:02:09,840 --> 01:02:11,592
There's an urgent telegram
for you.

710
01:02:15,320 --> 01:02:16,469
Here.

711
01:02:17,200 --> 01:02:19,191
Must be congratulations?
So soon?

712
01:02:24,320 --> 01:02:25,639
- Any answer?
- No.

713
01:02:26,520 --> 01:02:28,192
- What about the tip?
- Forget about it!

714
01:02:28,680 --> 01:02:30,557
What a detestable manner...

715
01:02:30,800 --> 01:02:34,110
... to bring bad news on
such a happy day?

716
01:02:54,960 --> 01:02:56,439
Yes...

717
01:02:58,840 --> 01:03:02,150
They haven't come.
I sound off retreat!

718
